 about her, and she said it was merely a bad dream after seeing a bad cinema film. Oh, you are not going yet, are you? She'll be back in a minute....' He looked at me and laughed (I think he had had a little too much of that brandy).

'Oh, I forget,' he said. 'It is not my present wife that you want to find. And by the way,' he added, 'my papers are in perfect order. I can show you my carte de travail.

And if you do find her, I should like to see her before she goes to prison. Or perhaps better